<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16900605-5">
               <interp inst="t16900605-5" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16900605-5" type="year" value="1690"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16900605-5" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16900605"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16900605-5" type="date" value="16900605"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16900605-5-off21-c34" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-defend41 t16900605-5-off21 t16900605-5-verdict25"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16900605-5-off21-c35" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-defend42 t16900605-5-off21 t16900605-5-verdict25"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16900605-5-defend41" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Goodson
                  <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend41" type="surname" value="Goodson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend41" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend41" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             as principal, and 
               <persName id="t16900605-5-defend42" type="defendantName">
                  Abraham 
                  Hartslop
               <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend42" type="surname" value="Hartslop"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend42" type="given" value="Abraham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-defend42" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             as Accessary, were both tryed for the <rs id="t16900605-5-off21" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-off21" type="offenceCategory" value="kill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-off21" type="offenceSubcategory" value="murder"></interp>
               Murther of one 
                     
                        <persName id="t16900605-5-victim44" type="victimName">
                           Bartholomew 
                           Long
                        <interp inst="t16900605-5-victim44" type="surname" value="Long"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16900605-5-victim44" type="given" value="Bartholomew"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16900605-5-victim44" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-off21 t16900605-5-victim44"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                   on the <rs id="t16900605-5-cd22" type="crimeDate">8th day of May</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-off21 t16900605-5-cd22"></join> last, giving him a mortal Bruise with a Quarter-Staff upon the head, of which he instantly died
            </rs>. The Evidence declared, that some rude Fellows viz White Fryers Men, were striving to get away some Goods out of the Prosecutor's house in <placeName id="t16900605-5-crimeloc23">Cow-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16900605-5-crimeloc23" type="placeName" value="Cow-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16900605-5-crimeloc23" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-off21 t16900605-5-crimeloc23"></join>, the Tenant, viz. a Broker, designing to make his Escape deceitfully into the Mint: But the Landlord interposing, they made a great Mutiny, and Riotous Tumult, threatning to be the death of any who should oppose them, and had several Quarter-staves, and short wooden pocket pistols, (as they term them) which are to be used in Chambers, or narrow places, with other Instruments of Cruelty.</p>
               <p>Goodson, was seen to strike the deceased with an Ashen Quarter staff about five Foot long, of which he immediately died. But it did not appear that Hart-slope struck any Blow. The Surgeon said that the deceased died of the Bruise. Goodson offer'd but little for himself, only that he was hired as a <rs id="t16900605-5-deflabel24" type="occupation">Porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900605-5-defend41 t16900605-5-deflabel24"></join> to get away the Goods <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16900605002"></xptr>and called some Evidence, who gave a fair account of his former Conversation. But there being but one Evidence that swore positively Goodson struck the Blow, a Debate arose between the Court and the Jury; afterwards they came to this Result, That the matter should at present be found <rs id="t16900605-5-verdict25" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16900605-5-verdict25" type="verdictCategory" value="specialVerdict"></interp>
               Special
            </rs>, &amp;c.</p>
            </div1>
